<bug>
	<id>565556</id>
	<title>Change Save to Download</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">(Note: this is filed as part of the “Paper Cut” bugs — we assume that there may be multiple existing bugs on this.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">Please make them block this bug, and we will de-dupe if they are indeed exactly the same.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">Thanks!)</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">To reproduce:</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">1 Start up Firefox</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">2 open up a new page</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.4">3 go to "File-&gt;Save Page As ....</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Recommendation:
We (the UX team) recommend changing all instances of "Save" to "Download".</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">Such as "Save image as" -&gt; "Download image as".</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">The term "download" is now very much part of the internet language.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
